Construction works for the Anantara Hotel Development Project are officially underway with the official signing of the project’s Memorandum of Understanding (MOU). When the Anantara Hotel Development Project is completed it will feature restaurants, various hotel brands, souk offerings as well as luxury retail brands. The Memorandum of Understanding for the Anantara Hotel Development Project was signed by Minor Hotels with the developer behind Saudi Arabia’s Diriyah Gate Giga project, Diriyah Gate Development Authority. The hotel will be under the company’s luxury brand known as the Anantara brand. When officially launched, the project is revealed to feature well over 100 restaurants, more than 400 luxury retail brands as well as 38 hotel brands. Currently, the hotel project is in its final stages of planning. The Founder and Chairman of Minor International, which is the parent company of Minor Hotels, William E. Heinecke happily stated that they are excited to be a part of the world’s most impressive and exciting collections of hotels within the Diriyah Gate. He further added that the Anantara Hotel Development Project was second to none in terms of both luxury and scale. He continued by saying that the hotel is focused on bringing a completely eccentric experience to both visitors and residents. The Founder and Chairman concluded by saying that they look forward to working with the team of the Diriyah Gate Development Authority in bringing the project to full fruition. Read Also Qiddiya Water Theme Park Project Updates, Saudi Arabia On the other hand, the group CEO of the Diriyah Gate Development Authority, Jerry Inzerillo commented that Anantara is one of the world’s most beloved brands and that their unique style of hospitality is the perfect fit for this project in particular. Jerry further added that the project will be a superb addition to what is set to be one of the greatest lifestyle destinations in the world.